  "why": "The paper goes beyond merely reporting failures: it characterizes properties of discovered jailbreaks (e.g., transferability across models, per-template ASR/EASR metrics, and the impact of seed-selection and mutator choices via ablation studies). These analyses provide partial diagnostic insight into failure patterns and which fuzzer design choices produce more failures. However, the paper does not trace failures to underlying model vulnerabilities (e.g., dataset bias, spurious features, or internal model signals); it offers hypotheses (e.g., Gemini’s robustness due to red-teaming) rather than evidence linking failures to root causes or internal model behavior. This matches the “Medium” level: characterization of failure properties without linking them to underlying model vulnerabilities.",
